entries.title: Ukraine war likely to 'go on for some time', warns US secretary of state
entries.description: Russia's war in Ukraine is likely to "go on for some time" and now is the moment to ramp up military aid, the US secretary of state has said.

entries.title: Germany should 'follow UK's example' and send us tanks, says Ukrainian deputy PM
entries.description: Talk to enough of the delegates gathered here in the Swiss town of Davos and the impression you pick up is a palpable sense of relief.

entries.title: Father filmed celebrating daughter's birthday - before he died in missile strike on same flat
entries.description: Footage has emerged of a Ukrainian father celebrating his daughter's birthday with candles and cake in a kitchen days before he was killed in a Russian missile strike in the same apartment.

entries.title: Meet the 'antidote to big man-ism' who could be Nigeria's next president
entries.description: He was relatively unknown until a few months ago, and yet Peter Obi has been propelled to frontrunner status in Nigeria's upcoming election.

entries.title: Microsoft to axe thousands of jobs in latest cull by tech giant
entries.description: Microsoft is preparing to axe thousands of jobs in the latest move by one of the world's biggest technology companies to reduce its workforce in the face of a slowing global economy.

entries.title: Greta Thunberg detained by police during eco protest in Germany
entries.description: Greta Thunberg has been detained by police during a demonstration in Germany.

entries.title: Elon Musk and Tesla going on trial over claims his tweets cost investors billions of dollars
entries.description: Elon Musk and Tesla are set to go on trial over allegations that shareholders were defrauded out of billions of dollars by his tweets.

entries.title: 'Insult to mankind': Ukrainian first lady criticises leaders at Davos
entries.description: Ukraine's first lady Olena Zelenska has called for an increased international effort to combat Russian aggression, saying it was an "insult to mankind" to have mass starvation.

entries.title: Breakthrough laser beam used to successfully divert lightning strikes
entries.description: In a development that would look right at home in a sci-fi disaster film, researchers have developed a laser beam that can divert lightning.

entries.title: French football president faces investigation over sexual harassment allegations
entries.description: The president of the French Football Federation (FFF) is to be investigated after allegations of "sexual and moral harassment" were made against him.

entries.title: Former Wagner Group member seeks asylum in Norway after fleeing Russia
entries.description: A Russian man, who is reportedly a former high-ranking member of Russian private military contractor Wagner Group, has sought asylum in Norway.

entries.title: Second Colorado library shuts due to meth contamination
entries.description: A second US library has been forced to shut due to meth contamination.

entries.title: 'The revolution is still alive': Diary of an Iranian student protesting against the regime
entries.description: "The revolution is still alive in people, and people are looking forward to a big change to this country."

entries.title: Andy Murray knocks Matteo Berrettini out of Australian Open
entries.description: Former Wimbledon champion Andy Murray has knocked seeded Matteo Berrettini out of the Australian Open after the final set went to a tie-break.

entries.title: China records first population decline in 60 years as birth rate plunges
entries.description: China has recorded its first population decline in six decades, as its birth rate plunged according to figures.

entries.title: Nepal co-pilot's husband also died in Yeti Airlines crash 16 years ago
entries.description: The co-pilot of Nepal's fatal plane crash had lost her husband who was a pilot in another Yeti Airlines accident 16 years ago.

entries.title: Cleverly aims to persuade US and Canada to send tanks to Ukraine on trip to North America
entries.description: Ukraine is set to be top of the agenda as Foreign Secretary James Cleverly begins a two-day trip to the US and Canada.
